All tests pass. The fix adds HTAB (horizontal tab, ASCII 9) support to align with RFC 9110's OWS definition.

**Changes made:**

1. `lib/content-type-parser.js` - Added check for HTAB (charCode 9) alongside space (charCode 32) when validating content-type before semicolon
2. `test/schema-validation.test.js` - Updated test expectation for `ApPlIcAtIoN/JsOn\t foo;` to expect 400 (validation error) instead of 415 (invalid media type), since HTAB is now valid whitespace per RFC 9110

